data and wants this information as soon as possible

19
00:01:22,529 --> 00:01:27,279
What should you do? Hadoop may be the answer

20
00:01:27,279 --> 00:01:30,630
What is Hadoop? Hadoop is an open source project of the Apache

21
00:01:30,630 --> 00:01:33,529
Foundation. It is a framework written in Java originally

22
00:01:33,529 --> 00:01:37,529
developed by Doug Cutting who named it after his son&#39;s toy elephant.

23
00:01:37,529 --> 00:01:41,109
Hadoop uses Google&#39;s MapReduce technology as its foundation.

24
00:01:41,109 --> 00:01:45,529
It is optimized to handle massive quantities of data which could be structured, unstructured

25
00:01:45,529 --> 00:01:51,569
or semi-structured, using commodity hardware, that is, relatively inexpensive computers.

26
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:54,959
This massive parallel processing is done with great performance. However, it is a batch

27
00:01:54,959 --> 00:02:00,229
operation handling massive amounts of data, so the response time is not immediate. Currently,

28
00:02:00,229 --> 00:02:04,529
in place updates are not possible in Hadoop, but appends to existing data is supported.

29
00:02:04,529 --> 00:02:09,030
Now, what&#39;s the value of a system if the information it stores or retrieves is not

30
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:12,580
consistent? Hadoop replicates its data across different

31
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:16,370
computers, so that if one goes down, the data is processed on one of the replicated computers.

32
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:21,780
Hadoop is not suitable for OnLine Transaction Processing workloads where data is randomly

33
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:24,540
accessed on structured data like a relational database.

34
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:29,090
Also, Hadoop is not suitable for OnLine Analytical Processing or Decision Support System workloads

35
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:33,610
where data is sequentially accessed on structured data like a relational database, to generate

36
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:38,500
reports that provide business intelligence. As of Hadoop version 2.6, updates are not

37
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:42,610
possible, but appends are possible. Hadoop is used for Big Data. It complements

38
00:02:42,610 --> 00:02:46,240
OnLine Transaction Processing and OnLine Analytical Processing.

39
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:50,050
It is NOT a replacement for a relational database system.

40
00:02:50,050 --> 00:02:55,080
So, what is Big Data? With all the devices available today to collect

41
00:02:55,080 --> 00:03:00,820
data, such as RFID readers, microphones, cameras, sensors, and so on, we are seeing an explosion

42
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:05,370
in data being collected worldwide. Big Data is a term used to describe large

43
00:03:05,370 --> 00:03:10,200
collections of data (also known as datasets) that may be unstructured, and grow so large

44
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:14,580
and quickly that it is difficult to manage with a regular database or statistical tools.

45
00:03:14,580 --> 00:03:19,790
In terms of numbers, what are we looking at? How BIG is &quot;big data&quot;?

46
